{
  "name": "1 · WBR: Weekly Callouts",
  "version": "4",
  "description": "Full WBR callout pipeline: ingest → analyst → writer → blind review → correction. 10 markets. Now with cross-channel signal context.",
  "when": { "type": "userTriggered" },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "Run full WBR callout pipeline. ISO week W{NN}.\n\nPREDICTION SCORING (do this FIRST): Read ~/shared/wiki/callouts/prediction-ledger.md. Find the most recent Source block with unscored predictions (Actual = '—'). If the target week's actuals are now available in ps.performance or in the data briefs from the ingester, score each prediction: fill in Actual, compute Error% = |predicted - actual| / actual × 100, and set Score (HIT if actual within CI, MISS if outside CI but within 20%, SURPRISE if >20% off). Save the updated ledger. This closes the feedback loop before generating new predictions.\n\nPREREQUISITE: Check if the WBR pipeline has already run for this week by reading ~/shared/tools/prediction/callout-signal.json. If the signal file exists and matches the current week, the pipeline has already ingested data, scored predictions, updated priors, and generated projections. Use the projections from ps.forecasts and pacing from ps.monthly_pacing in the callout drafts.\n\nIf no signal file exists, run the WBR pipeline first:\n  python3 ~/shared/tools/prediction/wbr_pipeline.py <xlsx_path> --week 2026-W{NN}\n\nFORECAST CONTEXT: After pipeline runs, query these views for callout context:\n- SELECT * FROM ps.latest_forecasts WHERE metric_name = 'registrations' — W{NN+1} predictions per market\n- SELECT * FROM ps.monthly_pacing — MTD vs OP2 for current month\n- SELECT * FROM ps.calibration_state — per-market calibration and CI width\nInclude vs OP2 regs AND spend in the monthly projection line: (vs. OP2: +X% regs, -Y% spend)\n\nCROSS-CHANNEL SIGNAL CONTEXT (from Phase 2.5 enrichment):\n- Query signal_tracker for market-relevant topics: SELECT topic, source_channel, source_author, source_preview, signal_strength FROM signals.signal_tracker WHERE is_active AND (topic ILIKE '%au%' OR topic ILIKE '%mx%' OR topic ILIKE '%oci%' OR topic ILIKE '%polaris%') ORDER BY signal_strength DESC\n- Query project_timeline for recent events per market: SELECT project_name, event_date, event_type, summary FROM main.project_timeline WHERE event_date >= CURRENT_DATE - INTERVAL '14 days' ORDER BY event_date DESC\n- Query meeting_series for latest session context: SELECT meeting_name, last_session_date, running_themes FROM main.meeting_series WHERE last_session_date >= CURRENT_DATE - INTERVAL '14 days'\n- Use signal evidence in callout narratives: if a topic has strength >= 3.0 and channel_spread >= 2, it's a confirmed trend worth mentioning. If project_timeline shows a recent decision or launch, reference it.\n- Read relevant meeting series files from ~/shared/wiki/meetings/ for strategic context (e.g., brandon-sync.md for AU LP decisions, deep-dive-debate.md for testing methodology context)\n\nOUTPUT DIRECTORY: ~/shared/wiki/callouts/ (per-market subdirectories, WW summary files in ww/). Do NOT write to context/active/callouts/.\n\nINGEST xlsx. CONTEXT LOAD. BROAD CONTEXT. ANALYSIS (10 market-analyst runs). WRITING (10 callout-writer runs, >66% confidence). BLIND REVIEW. CORRECTION below 66%. REPORT with AU/MX highlights."
  }
}